Commentary Text: Russell to Manish Pandey, out Caught&Bowled!! A high full toss at 139.4kph, and is Manish Pandey is out caught-and-bowled? The umpires send it upstairs. It's below the waist and Pandey has to walk back. This is a big wicket. A full toss just below the waist from round the wicket, Pandey was initially looking to run it down to third man and later decided to work it into the on-side. Commentary Text: Chakravarthy to Warner, out Caught&Bowled!! First IPL scalp for Varun Chakravarthy in this edition of IPL. And it's the big fish - Warner. A blip in concentration for SRH's captain after the break. A nothing shot really. This gave an impression of stopping upon reaching the batsman. Teased Warner into pushing at it, he went a bit too hard and chips it back to the bowler. Chakravarthy doesn't drop those. It was catching practice indeed. KKR camp are elated. Warner c and b Chakravarthy 36(30) [4s-2 6s-1]

Commentary Text: Rashid Khan to Karthik, out Lbw!! Celeb appeal and the umpire's finger goes up for LBW. Think DK was happy to go, but he then chatted with his partner and decided to review. Pretty sure the 15-second time gap had elapsed, but here we go. It's a fair delivery and there's no inside edge on that. Was the wrong 'un and DK didn't read it one bit. UltraEdge confirms that there's no bat on that, Hawk-Eye in and it's three REDS. Karthik is OUT and KKR have wasted their review. Lovely delivery from Khan, slipped in the wrong 'un and Karthik didn't spot it - ended up playing outside the line as he lunged forward. Past the inside edge and struck adjacent to middle, was going on and crashing into the middle-stump. SRH keep themselves in the hunt with timely wickets. Karthik lbw b Rashid Khan 0(3)

Commentary Text: Khaleel Ahmed to Narine, out Caught by Warner!! The start SRH would have wanted after being restricted to a modest score. Look at Warner go, he's pumped up, this could lift his team as well. Back of a length and at the stumps, Narine was slightly cramped up on the pull, gets a steepling top-edge towards mid-off and Warner made sure that everyone else stayed away. Watched it all along and held on, a fist pump from Khaleel Ahmed as he exults. Narine c Warner b Khaleel Ahmed 0(2)
